Anniversary of Kim Il Sung's Work Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- It is the strong will of the Korean people to firmly preserve, widely use and develop their written and spoken languages closely associated with the leadership of the peerlessly great persons and thus further demonstrate the dignity and advantages of the Korean nation.
 Rodong Sinmun Sunday says this in a signed article.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 President Kim Il Sung authored the work "On Correctly Preserving the National Characteristics of the Korean Language" on May 14, Juche 55 (1966). The work has served as important guidelines as it gives comprehensive and scientific answers to the principled questions arising in preserving the national character and Juche character of the Korean language. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Clarified in the work in detail are the idea that it is an essential demand for the development of the Korean language and a national duty for the revolutionaries and other people to preserve its national character, the idea on the main orientation of properly preserving its national character and laying a foundation for developing it, the way of arranging and developing the Korean language and various issues in arranging the vocabulary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work sets out it as a very important idea to preserve and develop the national character of the Korean language with the speech of Pyongyang as its standard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il has creditably carried forward Kim Il Sung's Juche-oriented idea of language. He profoundly elucidated the essential principle and scientific ways for developing the socialist national language and clarified the issues to be settled by the party of the working class to develop the national language. And he has wisely led the work to firmly preserve the Juche character and national character in the linguistic life as required by the demand of the developing revolution in the new century, in particular, in which the building of a great prosperous powerful nation is now making dynamic progress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary and national way of linguistic life which calls for firmly preserving the Korean language and the cultured language prevails among our people.

Visiting Chinese Delegation Feted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- The DPRK government hosted a banquet at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Saturday in honor of a Chinese delegation of martyr Mao Anying's family and his relatives on a visit to the DPRK.
 Present there on invitation were the delegation led by former Deputy Department Director of the Chinese Academy of Military Science Shao Hua and Ambassador Wu Donghe, Military Attache Yang Xilian and staff members of the Chinese embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present were Vice-President of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly Yang Hyong Sop, Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Yong Il, Lieutenant General of the Korean People's Army Han Tong Gun, Secretary General of the Korean Committee of Anti-Imperialist Veteran Fighters An Yong Gi, officials concerned and KPA officers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Han Tong Gun in his speech made at the banquet recalled that the party and government of China headed by Mao Zedong organized the Chinese People's Volunteers and dispatched them to the Korean front 56 years back, adding that Mao Anying dedicated his life at the age of 28 while fighting as an ordinary CPV fighter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-China friendship has steadily grown stronger under the special care of leader Kim Jong Il and President Hu Jintao, he said, stressing that the Korean people are satisfied to see the successful inheritance of the DPRK-China friendship, a precious legacy Kim Il Sung provided and handed down together with revolutionaries of the elder generation of China including Mao Zedong, the great leader of the Chinese people, to posterity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Shao Hua in a speech said that the army and people of the DPRK have achieved great successes in the efforts to build a prosperous and powerful country and made progress in the work to improve the external environment in recent years, overcoming all difficulties by displaying the spirit of self-reliance and fortitude under the leadership of Kim Jong Il and the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the common desire of the peoples of the two countries and in line with their fundamental interests to steadily develop the Sino-Korean friendship, she noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I and the families and relatives of the fallen CPV fighters and all other Chinese comrades together with the Korean comrades will make all efforts to boost the traditional relations of the Sino-Korean friendship, setting store by them.

Protection of Phyongthaek Called for in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- The Presidium of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification reportedly issued a special appeal titled "Let us defend Phyongthaek for independence and peace of the Korean nation and our future" on May 9.
 The appeal said that Phyongthaek has witnessed the wild ambition of the U.S. to reduce it to a base for a war and proves how far the present "government" has gone in its pro-U.S. actions to indiscriminately kill its people, yielding to the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Phyongthaek requires the people to unite closer in the actions against the U.S., the appeal said, calling on all of them to rise up to defend Phyongthaek. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal denounced the present "government" keen to sacrifice its people for ensuring the expansion of the U.S. military base and the U.S. busy with its moves to reduce the Korean Peninsula to a military base for aggression. It demanded the withdrawal of the U.S. troops from south Korea.

Brutal Crackdown upon Protesters Assailed in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- The fact-finding group for probing the truth behind violence and violation of human rights in Phyongthaek of south Korea reportedly held a press conference in Seoul on May 10 to make public the initial results of investigation into the truth behind human rights abuses in Phyongthaek.
 The group said that the military and police forces, when requisitioning the land, tramped under their jackboots and blackjacked those involved in a sit-in strike and spread liquid tear gas over them, thus wounding more than 460 on May 4 and at least 100 on May 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also noted that the forces even barred those wounded from receiving the first-aid treatment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Terming the above-said crackdown premeditated, the group strongly demanded that the "government", the "Defense Ministry" and the police authorities take full responsibility for it and withdraw the forces from the site planned for the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It declared that it would form a litigious group of people to file a suit demanding the withdrawal of the defined "zone for the protection of military facilities" and sue the minister of Defense and the chief of the Police Office for spearheading such violence. It added that it would make public the second results of the investigation conducted into the truth behind the incident.

Floral Tribute Paid to Fallen CPV Fighters 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- The visiting Chinese delegation of martyr Mao Anying's family and his relatives headed by former Deputy Department Director of the Chinese Academy of Military Science Shao Hua traveled to Hoechang County, South Phyongan Province, on Sunday where it laid wreaths before the grave of Mao Anying and the cemetery of fallen fighters of the Chinese People's Volunteers.
 Present there were Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, An Yong Gi, secretary general of the Korean Committee of Anti-Imperialist Veteran Fighters, officials concerned, KPA officers, officials of Party and power bodies in the county, Wu Donghe, Chinese ambassador to the DPRK, Yang Xilian, military attache of the Chinese embassy, and its staff members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths in the name of the delegation, the embassy and the family and relatives of martyr Mao Anying were placed before the grave and wreaths in the name of the delegation and the embassy before the cemetery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The attendants paid silent tribute to Mao Anying and other fallen fighters of the CPV who laid down their lives while courageously fighting in the Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they looked round the grave and cemetery and planted trees around them.

DPRK-Syria Joint Economic Committee Meets 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- The 4th meeting of the DPRK-Syria Joint Economic Committee took place here on May 13 and 14.
 Present there were members of a DPRK government economic delegation headed by Minister of Foreign Trade Rim Kyong Man and members of a Syrian government economic delegation headed by Minister of Economy and Commerce Amer Hosni Lutfi and Syrian Charge d'Affaires ad Interim in Pyongyang Muhammad Adib Al Hani. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting reviewed the implementation of the protocol of the 3rd meeting of the committee and discussed issues of boosting the bilateral cooperation in the fields of economy, trade, science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The protocol of the 4th meeting of the DPRK-Syria Joint Economic Committee on cooperation in economic trade and science and technology was signed.

Wreaths Laid before Cemetery of Fallen CPV Fighters 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 14 (KCNA) -- The DPRK government and the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces and party and power bodies in Hoechang County, South Phyongan Province, laid wreaths before the cemetery of fallen fighters of the Chinese People's Volunteers in the county on Sunday.
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Yong Il, Secretary General of the Korean Committee of Anti-Imperialist Veteran Fighters An Yong Gi, officials concerned, KPA officers and officials of party and power bodies in the county. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths in the name of the DPRK government and the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces and party and power bodies in the county were placed before the cemetery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants paid silent tribute to the fallen CPV fighters, who courageously fought for the great victory in the sacred war against the U.S., together with the KPA after rushing to the Korean war under the banner of "Resisting America, Aiding Korea, Safeguarding the Home and Defending the Motherland".

Letter to Kim Jong Il Adopted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 13 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il received a letter sent by the participants of a meeting of communist parties and friendship and solidarity organizations in the Nordic countries on Apr. 13 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 The letter said:  On the occasion of the 94th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung we remember with deep emotion the enormous efforts made by him for the reunification of the country and the exploits performed by him in this cause during his lifetime. We express invariable solidarity with the Korean people in their struggle for reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The three principles of independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity and the proposal for achieving reunification by a federal formula set forth by Kim Il Sung are a reasonable offer acceptable to anyone desirous of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If peace is to settle on the Korean Peninsula the U.S. should replace the armistice agreement by a peace mechanism, the Korean people should wage a dynamic patriotic movement for independent reunification, peace against war and great national unity in the idea of "By our nation itself" and accelerate Korea's reunification under the banner of the June 15 joint declaration.

Crackdown upon Struggle against Expansion of U.S. Military Base in Phyongthaek Denounced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 13 (KCNA) -- The All-People Measure Committee for Checking the Expansion of the U.S. Military Base in Phyongthaek of south Korea reportedly issued a statement on May 9 to denounce the "Ministry of National Defence" for its crackdown and the conservative media for its false report.
 The statement accused the ministry of supplying lethal equipment to the south Korean army unit mobilized to ensure the expansion of the base and threatening to apply the military law to those struggling against the expansion on May 8. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the ministry is instigating the conservative media to drive a wedge between the inhabitants in Phyongthaek and the measure committee and describe the actions of the people against the requisitioning of land and eviction as "violent actions of the anti-U.S. forces" in a bid to secure a pretext for harsh crackdown upon them, the statement charged. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement demanded the "government" immediately withdraw the army unit and remove wire entanglements, retract the unreasonable designation of the "zone for the protection of military facilities", take responsibility for the brutal crackdown, fire the minister of "National Defence" and the chief of the police agency and release all those arrested. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement bitterly denounced the conservative media for turning their faces away from the essence and danger of the situation and releasing grossly distorted reports about what happened in Phyongthaek without having even an iota of impartiality as media.

Conservative Media's Diatribe under Fire in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 13 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon) reportedly released a statement on May 9 to denounce the conservative media for speaking ill of the conference of representatives of the students in the north and the south for the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration.
 The statement expressed anger at the conservative media's ridiculous act of misinterpreting the significance of the conference of representatives of the south and the north, the first of its kind in the history of national division, at which they reiterated the will to work hard for the reunification and peace of the country and misleading the public opinion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nothing is more deplorable than the anachronistic attitude of the conservative media branding the just patriotic activities of the students as pro-north and anti-U.S. ones, the statement noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With no desperate obstructions can the anti-reunification forces stop the Koreans from advancing towards reunification by their concerted efforts. Hanchongryon will join the patriotic students of other universities in spearheading the movement for implementing the June 15 joint declaration.

Russian Ambassador Hosts Reception
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 13 (KCNA) -- Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Andrei Karlov Friday hosted a reception at the Russian embassy on the occasion of the 61st anniversary of Russia's victory in the Great Patriotic War.
 Present on invitation were officials concerned and officers of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were staff members of the Russian embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the reception.

Moves to Strengthen U.S.-Japan Military Alliance Denounced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 13 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Committee for Asian Joint Action against the U.S. and Japanese Imperialists' Aggression and Domination in Asia reportedly issued a statement on May 3 to denounce the U.S. and Japan for scheming to strengthen their military alliance.
 Recalling that the U.S. and Japan agreed to set up joint headquarters on May 2, the statement said that through this the U.S. is seeking to make Japan a strategic stronghold for aggression in Northeast Asia and Japan is intending to put into practice a war of aggression with the strengthened military alliance with the U.S. as a springboard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is keen to strengthen the U.S.-Japan alliance through the joint headquarters and, at the same time, expand its influence, spread the theatre of activity of the "Self-Defence Forces" all over the world and make it possible to interfere in case of "emergency" in the Korean Peninsula, the statement pointed out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement charged that the agreement of the U.S. and Japan to set up the join headquarters is certainly to drive the Korean Peninsula into a vortex of war.

Rodong Sinmun on Era of Songun Politics
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 13 (KCNA) -- The era of Songun is an era of enormous creation and change in which the army and people in the DPRK are working hard in all fields to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation. Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article.
 Thanks to the Songun policy of the Workers' Party of Korea the servicepersons and people have put the overall economy on the track of steady progress, pulling through grave difficulties in recent years, the article notes, and says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun policy, in short, means a socialist political mode that makes it possible to defend the country and push ahead with socialist construction in all aspects by putting forward the People's Army as the main force of revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation is a high goal our Party set while developing in depth the Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A great prosperous powerful socialist nation we are building in the era of Songun means, in a word, a great country whose national strength is strong, where everything is thriving and people have no more to desire in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The validity and creative might of our Party's Songun political mode have been fully proven in the practice of building a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is now making the biggest creations and changes startling the world people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The era of Songun is an era of the all-round efflorescence and development of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun policy has helped not only increase the military muscle in every way but augment the national power in politics, economy, culture and all other fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the era of Songun our country has witnessed leaping progress in different fields of socialist construction, including economy and culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The era of Songun is an era seething with the drive for creation and construction aimed at achieving eternal prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our army and people are now effecting a great Songun revolutionary surge on all fronts in hearty response to the militant call of the WPK for making a fresh leap forward in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The greatest success made in the drive for creation and change in the era of Songun is possible only thanks to the wise guidance of the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il is a genius of creation and construction without a parallel in history. His distinguished creative spirit finds its expression in the fact that he sets a high goal and makes an increasingly exact demand in every undertaking. Whatever is to be produced or built, he makes sure that it is done on the highest level in the world to be admired by posterity. It is also reflected in his rare sweep which makes it possible to achieve the greatest success in the shortest span of time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The drive for creation and change in the era of Songun is very dynamic as it is propelled by the might of single-minded unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun policy has helped to turn our revolutionary ranks into ranks strong in the revolutionary spirit and militancy. The leader unrolls a grandiose blueprint for national prosperity while the army and the people devotedly carry through the Party's line and policies. And they are united close as one in mind to make a breakthrough for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. Herein lies a secret to all miracles taking place in Songun Korea.

U.S. Can Never Cover Up Its True Colors as Biological and Chemical War Criminal
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 13 (KCNA) -- The U.S. bellicose forces, not content with being the biggest possessor of biological and chemical weapons in the world, are continuously developing and producing new nuclear, biological and chemical weapons and openly using them in aggression and war against other countries in defiance of international law.
 Citing data, a signed article of Rodong Sinmun Saturday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists committed a germ and chemical warfare in a real earnest in the northern half of Korea during the last Korean War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. Joint Chiefs of Staff mapped out a plan for extensively using germ weapons in the actual war in the autumn of 1950. On this basis they committed a germ warfare against peaceable residents and cities of Korea in a wily way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The germ warfare atrocities of the U.S. troops reached the extremes in 1952. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They dropped all sorts of germ bombs on 169 areas of the northern half of Korea 804 times in total from early January to March 1952. They dropped various articles containing poisonous insects and germs in at least 90 cities and counties 900 times in total from January to April 1952. Kinds of the germ weapons used by them during the war numbered more than 20. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They not only massively used germ weapons during the war but also brutally conducted tests on living bodies of POWs of our side. In 1951 they sent warships to a place near Wonsan, where they tested germ weapons on POWs almost every day, totaling 3,000 cases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  One of the most brutal crimes committed by the U.S. imperialists against Koreans during the war was that they massively used chemical weapons. They used many chemical weapons in 24 cities and counties in the northern half of Korea including Kangwon and Hwanghae Provinces and front areas from February 1951 to July 1953. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Napalm bombs were used in most cases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They used depleted uranium shells and other weapons of mass destruction in the Vietnam war, Persian Gulfs war and in the subsequent wars, inflicting great casualties and sufferings upon a large number of people. They brutally killed peaceable people of Iraq with chemical weapons on charges of "terrorists".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The biological and chemical warfare committed by the U.S. imperialists, the most diabolic and cruel barbarians of modern type, can never be covered up. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is the biggest possessor of biological and chemical weapons in the world. Nevertheless, the U.S. imperialists try to brand others as criminals, an indication of their peculiar shamelessness and brigandism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should stop unreasonable action of finding fault with others who are not problematic, honestly admit and open to the public its atrocious crimes of biological and chemical warfare and stand trial by history.

Wreaths Placed before Friendship Tower
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 13 (KCNA) -- A Chinese delegation of martyr Mao Anying's family and his relatives led by former Deputy Department Director of the Chinese Academy of Military Science Shao Hua laid a wreath before the Friendship Tower on Saturday.
  Present there were Chinese Ambassador to the DPRK Wu Donghe, Military Attache of the Chinese Embassy Yang Xilian and embassy officials, Secretary General of the Korean Committee of Anti-Imperialist Veteran Fighters An Yong Gi, officials concerned and officers of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of a wreath-laying music a wreath in the name of the delegation was placed before the tower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the wreath were letters "Fallen fighters of the Heroic Chinese People's Volunteers will be immortal"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants paid silent tribute to those CPV fighters who fell while courageously fighting in the last Korean war before looking round the tower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head of the delegation made the following entry in the visitor's book: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Let us carry forward the Sino-Korea friendship generation after generation to honor the memory of the forerunners"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a wreath was laid before the tower by a delegation of the China Chamber of International Commerce headed by Chairman of the China Council for the Promotion of International Trade Wan Jifei on the same day.

Visits
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 13 (KCNA) -- A delegation of the Bureau of Diplomatic Corps Affairs headed by its Director Kim Tang Su, a delegation of the State Bureau for Quality Control led by its Director Kim Hyong Chol and a delegation of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea headed by Won Hyong Guk, vice-chairman of its Central Committee, left here Saturday for China.
 A delegation of the China Development Bank headed by its Governor Chen Yuan and Senior Vice-President of the International Taekwon-Do Federation Ri Ki Ha and his party to attend celebrations of the 40th founding anniversary of the federation arrived here on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also arriving here were Chinese delegations including a delegation of the China Chamber of International Commerce headed by Chairman of the China Council for the Promotion of International Trade Wan Jifei, delegations of Syria, Thailand, Spain, Sweden, France, Switzerland, Germany and Taipei of China to participate in the 9th Pyongyang International Spring Commodity Fair. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Czech and Italian delegations arrived earlier.
